EDITORS COMMENTS

In this print titled "Former bassist of The Animals pop group Chas Chandler talks about the building of the Newcastle Arena" we are transported back to a significant moment in music history. Taken on November 20,1995, this image captures the legendary musician and former member of The Animals, Chas Chandler, as he passionately discusses the construction of what would become an iconic venue. With his charismatic presence and undeniable talent, Chas Chandler played a pivotal role in shaping the sound and success of one of Britain's most influential pop groups during the 1960s. Now, years later, we see him lending his expertise to another musical endeavor - sharing insights into the development of Newcastle Arena. As he stands before an eager audience, it is evident that Chas Chandler's passion for music remains unwavering. His animated gestures and expressive face reflect a deep connection to both his own musical journey and the vibrant industry that continues to evolve around him. This photograph from Memory Lane Prints not only captures a specific moment in time but also serves as a testament to the enduring legacy left by musicians like Chas Chandler. It reminds us that behind every great performance or groundbreaking venue lies countless hours of dedication and hard work from individuals who have shaped our collective musical experience.
